            { level: 2, title: "The Pilot Project Patron", meaning: "You've got a formal strategy on paper and maybe even a designated 'AI champion.' However, you're stuck in pilot mode. A key challenge in the Finnish market is 'insufficient investment for scaling.' You can prove a concept but struggle to get the resources to make it a core part of the business.", next_step: "Focus on one successful pilot and create a detailed scaling plan. Show not just the tech, but the impact on P&L. Advocate for the creation of a formal CAIO (Chief AI Officer) role, as discussed in the 'CAIO Community Building' analysis, to provide centralized leadership and secure dedicated, long-term funding." },
            { level: 3, title: "The Business Integrator", meaning: "You're ahead of the curve! AI is integrated into business unit strategies, and you're actively trying to break out of the '1% of companies creating new business from data' slump seen in Finland. You're moving from cost-saving to value-creation.", next_step: "Double down on innovation. Use your established AI foundation to explore creating entirely new, data-driven revenue streams. Foster a culture of 'vibe leading,' where managers are augmented by AI to make faster, more data-driven strategic decisions, as outlined in the 'AI-Driven Leadership' report." },
            { level: 4, title: "The Market Shaper", meaning: "Your leadership, including a strong CAIO, uses AI as a primary weapon for competitive advantage. You're not just optimizing processes; you're using AI for R&D, new product invention, and to dictate the pace of your industry.", next_step: "Expand your influence. Use your leadership position to build cross-industry and cross-Nordic collaborations, as highlighted in the 'CAIO Community' analysis. Your next frontier is to move towards a fully 'rewired' organization where AI isn't just a tool but the core operating system of your strategy." },
            { level: 5, title: "The AI-Native Executive", meaning: "Strategy is no longer an annual process; it's a real-time, AI-augmented dialogue. Your leadership practices 'vibe leading' at its peak, using agentic platforms to model complex scenarios and drive autonomous execution. You don't react to the market; the market reacts to you.", next_step: "Your challenge is now philosophical and ethical. Focus on establishing 'Ethics by Design' as a global standard. Lead the conversation on the societal impact of fully agentic enterprises and help define the next generation of responsible AI governance. Your organization is now a case study." }
        ],
        "People & Skills": [
            { level: 1, title: "The Lone Enthusiast", meaning: "You have a massive AI skills gap. Any AI usage is driven by a few isolated enthusiasts, creating a 'digital divide' within your workforce. As the 'AI Skills Gap' analysis points out, this is a huge barrier to any real transformation.", next_step: "Start with literacy. Launch a broad-based, accessible training program like Finland's 'Elements of AI' course for all employees. The goal isn't to make everyone a data scientist, but to create a common language and understanding of AI's potential and risks." },
            { level: 2, title: "The Talent Hunter", meaning: "You recognize the skills gap, but your primary strategy is trying to hire your way out of it, which is difficult given Finland's shortage of 15,000 data experts. You're overlooking the potential of your current workforce and creating a two-tiered system of 'AI haves' and 'have-nots.'", next_step: "Shift from recruiting to reskilling. Prioritize upskilling your current employees. A key strategy is to adopt a skills-first approach. Use a platform like Talbit's Skillbit, as analyzed in the documents, to visualize your current skills, identify gaps, and create clear career paths for your existing talent." },
            { level: 3, title: "The Upskilling Machine", meaning: "You're actively building talent, not just buying it. You have formal, large-scale upskilling programs (like PwC's 'My AI') and are mapping competencies. Your developers are evolving from coders to 'AI Collaborators.'", next_step: "Go from broad training to precision deployment. Integrate learning into daily workflows. Focus on creating hybrid 'tech-plus-business' talent to bridge the gap between your technical teams and business strategy. This ensures your training investment translates directly into business value." },
            { level: 4, title: "The Hybrid Team Builder", meaning: "Your people are your strategic advantage. You provide continuous, personalized AI coaching and have intentionally designed new career paths for roles impacted by AI. You are building deeply integrated, cross-functional teams where everyone is AI-literate.", next_step: "Prepare for the next evolution: the fully agentic workplace. Your focus should now be on training your teams to manage and collaborate with autonomous AI agents. This involves developing skills in supervision, exception handling, and designing human-in-the-loop systems." },
            { level: 5, title: "The Talent Ecosystem", meaning: "Your organization is a talent magnet. AI-driven platforms manage personalized career paths, coaching, and team formation. New roles like 'AI Code Auditor' are standard. You don't just have skilled people; you have a self-improving talent ecosystem.", next_step: "Your role is now to cultivate the broader ecosystem. Partner with universities and government initiatives (like the 'Data Skills microdegree' in Finland) to shape the next generation of talent for the entire industry. You are not just a company; you are a talent factory." }
        ],
        "Technology & Data": [
            { level: 1, title: "The Data Hoarder", meaning: "Your data is a mess—siloed, inconsistent, and probably stored on a server under someone's desk. You have a high rate of cloud adoption, but it's just a digital filing cabinet. You're part of the 99% of Finnish firms not creating new business from data.", next_step: "Start with one thing: data quality. Pick one critical business area and focus on cleaning and consolidating its data. Establish a basic data governance framework. You can't build a skyscraper on a swamp." },
            { level: 2, title: "The 'Vibe Coding' Dabbler", meaning: "You're using AI to build things quickly, which is great for prototypes. The downside? As the 'AI-Driven Development' analysis warns, you are creating 'the largest accumulation of technical debt in history.' Your codebase is becoming a tangled, unmaintainable mess.", next_step: "Introduce discipline. Keep the speed of 'vibe coding' for non-critical prototypes, but establish a rule: no AI-generated code enters production without a rigorous human review and passing through an automated testing and security pipeline. Start tracking your technical debt." },
            { level: 3, title: "The Platform Adopter", meaning: "You've matured. You're using enterprise-grade AI platforms (like EY.ai or Microsoft Fabric) and have implemented MLOps. You have a hybrid development model that balances the speed of AI generation with the discipline of DevOps.", next_step: "Focus on differentiation. Move beyond off-the-shelf tools and start building proprietary, industry-specific AI solutions that give you a unique competitive advantage. Leverage Finland's high-performance computing infrastructure, like the LUMI supercomputer, for more advanced model development." },
            { level: 4, title: "The AI Innovator", meaning: "Your tech stack is a strategic asset. You're building your own proprietary models and using AI-powered tools to manage your AI, including automated QA and security agents that review code. You are a leader in your industry's use of technology.", next_step: "Push the frontier to Agentic AI. Begin experimenting with autonomous agents that can orchestrate complex, multi-step workflows across your enterprise systems. This is the next major shift beyond generative AI, moving from content creation to autonomous action." },
            { level: 5, title: "The Agentic Architect", meaning: "Your technology is practically alive. A system of autonomous AI agents manages your entire development lifecycle, from ideation to deployment and maintenance. Your stack is a self-healing, self-optimizing ecosystem. The 'vibe coding' dream is now a safe, automated reality.", next_step: "Your main technological challenge is managing the immense complexity and potential emergent behavior of multi-agent systems. Your focus shifts from building tools to systems theory, orchestration, and ensuring the resilience of your highly autonomous digital workforce." }
        ],
        "Governance & Risk": [
            { level: 1, title: "The Risk Ignorer", meaning: "AI Governance? Is that a new TV show? Your leadership is unaware of the significant risks of AI, from security vulnerabilities to data bias and IP infringement. You're flying blind and are a data breach or a PR disaster waiting to happen.", next_step: "Start with education. Conduct a workshop for leadership on the key risks of AI, using real-world examples. Focus on one critical area, like the security risks of 'vibe coding' (e.g., hardcoded secrets, SQL injection) and establish a basic policy for reviewing AI-generated code." },
            { level: 2, title: "The Anxious Adopter", meaning: "You're aware of the risks, and frankly, they scare you. You have some ethical guidelines on a document somewhere, but as the 'CAIO Community' analysis notes, accountability is unclear. You're worried about the EU AI Act but don't have a concrete plan.", next_step: "Establish clear accountability. Form a cross-functional AI governance task force with members from legal, IT, and business units. Their first task: conduct a risk assessment of your current AI usage and create a prioritized action plan for compliance with the EU AI Act." },
            { level: 3, title: "The Framework Builder", meaning: "You're taking governance seriously. You have a formal AI governance framework, an ethics board, and you've embedded automated security scanning (SAST/SCA) into your CI/CD pipeline to check all AI-generated code before deployment.", next_step: "Move from reactive defense to proactive trust-building. Implement a dedicated Responsible AI platform (like EY's Trusted AI Platform) to continuously monitor your models for bias, drift, and fairness in real-time. Make your commitment to responsible AI a public part of your brand." },
            { level: 4, title: "The Trust Leader", meaning: "Responsible AI is a core part of your company's identity and a competitive advantage. You may even have a dedicated Al Ethics Officer. You're not just complying with regulations; you're helping to shape them.", next_step: "Your next step is to automate trust. Explore 'AI-to-AI feedback cycles,' where one AI agent is responsible for auditing and validating the work of another. This creates a scalable system of checks and balances that can keep pace with high-velocity, AI-driven development." },
            { level: 5, title: "The Ethical Pioneer", meaning: "'Ethics by Design' is your default operating principle. Governance isn't a checklist; it's embedded in every tool, process, and algorithm. Trust in your AI systems is a key performance indicator that you measure and report on.", next_step: "You are setting the standard. Your role is now to lead the industry in establishing best practices for the governance of highly autonomous, agentic AI systems. Collaborate with regulators and academia to help build the frameworks that will ensure the next generation of AI is developed responsibly." }
        ]
    },
    // SVG icons
    svgs: {
        welcomeMascot: `<svg viewBox="0 0 100 100" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><g transform="translate(0, -5)"><path d="M25,95 C20,80 20,60 25,45 L75,45 C80,60 80,80 75,95 Z" fill="#374151"/><rect x="40" y="30" width="20" height="20" rx="5" fill="#4f46e5"/><path d="M42,35 h16" stroke="white" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"/><path d="M42,40 h16" stroke="white" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"/><path d="M42,45 h10" stroke="white" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"/><rect x="20" y="50" width="60" height="10" rx="3" fill="#1f2937"/><rect x="15" y="45" width="70" height="10" rx="3" fill="#111827"/><path d="M30 60 L25 75 L40 75 Z" fill="#4f46e5"/><path d="M70 60 L75 75 L60 75 Z" fill="#4f46e5"/><path d="M40 75 L60 75 L60 90 L40 90 Z" fill="#4b5563"/><path d="M45,90 v5" stroke="#374151" stroke-width="2"/><path d="M55,90 v5" stroke="#374151" stroke-width="2"/><g id="sunglasses" transform="translate(0, -2)"><path d="M25 47 C 35 40, 45 40, 50 47 L 45 50 L 25 50 Z" fill="black"/><path d="M75 47 C 65 40, 55 40, 50 47 L 55 50 L 75 50 Z" fill="black"/><path d="M50 47 H 52" stroke="black" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round"/></g></g></svg>`,
        surfboard: `<svg width="40" height="40" viewBox="0 0 100 100"><path d="M50 0 C 80 20, 80 80, 50 100 C 20 80, 20 20, 50 0 Z" fill="#fb923c" transform="rotate(45 50 50)"/><path d="M30 70 L 70 30" stroke="white" stroke-width="5" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg>`
    }
};


// --- APPLICATION LOGIC ---
document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
    // Element references
    const app = document.getElementById('app');
    const welcomeScreen = document.getElementById('welcome-screen');
    const assessmentScreen = document.getElementById('assessment-screen');
    const resultsScreen = document.getElementById('results-screen');
    const questionContainer = document.getElementById('question-container');
    const startBtn = document.getElementById('start-btn');
    const backBtn = document.getElementById('back-btn');
    const nextBtn = document.getElementById('next-btn');
    const retakeBtn = document.getElementById('retake-btn');
    const shareBtn = document.getElementById('share-btn');
    const progressBar = document.getElementById('progress-bar');
    const progressSurfboard = document.getElementById('progress-surfboard');
    const mascotWelcome = document.getElementById('mascot-welcome');
    
    // Modal elements
    const modal = document.getElementById('modal');
    const closeModalBtn = document.getElementById('close-modal-btn');
    const modalTitle = document.getElementById('modal-title');
    const modalLevel = document.getElementById('modal-level');
    const modalMeaning = document.getElementById('modal-meaning');
    const modalNextStep = document.getElementById('modal-next-step');

    // State
    let currentPillarIndex = 0;
    let userAnswers = {}; // {0: {main: 1, followup: 1}, 1: {main: 3}}
    let resultsChart = null;

    // --- INITIALIZATION ---
    
    function init() {
        // Inject SVGs
        mascotWelcome.innerHTML = assessmentData.svgs.welcomeMascot;
        progressSurfboard.innerHTML = assessmentData.svgs.surfboard;

        // Add event listeners
        startBtn.addEventListener('click', startAssessment);
        nextBtn.addEventListener('click', handleNext);
        backBtn.addEventListener('click', handleBack);
        retakeBtn.addEventListener('click', resetAssessment);
        shareBtn.addEventListener('click', () => alert('Sharing functionality would be implemented here!'));
        closeModalBtn.addEventListener('click', () => modal.classList.add('hidden', 'opacity-0'));
        modal.addEventListener('click', (e) => {
            if (e.target === modal) {
                modal.classList.add('hidden', 'opacity-0');
            }
        });
    }
    
    // --- ASSESSMENT FLOW ---

    function startAssessment() {
        welcomeScreen.classList.add('hidden');
        assessmentScreen.classList.remove('hidden');
        currentPillarIndex = 0;
        userAnswers = {};
        renderQuestion();
        updateProgress();
    }

    function resetAssessment() {
        resultsScreen.classList.add('hidden');
        welcomeScreen.classList.remove('hidden');
        if (resultsChart) {
            resultsChart.destroy();
        }
        // Stop any ongoing speech
        window.speechSynthesis.cancel();
    }

    // --- RENDERING ---

    function renderQuestion() {
        const pillar = assessmentData.pillars[currentPillarIndex];
        const answerForPillar = userAnswers[currentPillarIndex] || {};
        const currentFollowupKey = answerForPillar.followupKey;
        
        const isFollowupView = currentFollowupKey && pillar.followups[currentFollowupKey];
        const questionData = isFollowupView ? pillar.followups[currentFollowupKey] : pillar;
        
        // BUG FIX: Correctly reference mainQuestion for main view
        const questionText = isFollowupView ? questionData.question : questionData.mainQuestion;

        let answersHtml = questionData.answers.map((answer) => {
            const isSelected = isFollowupView 
                ? answerForPillar.followupValue === answer.value
                : answerForPillar.mainValue === answer.value;

            return `
                <div 
                    class="answer-option bg-gray-700 p-4 rounded-lg cursor-pointer border-2 border-transparent hover:border-indigo-500 transition-all ${isSelected ? 'border-indigo-500 bg-indigo-900' : ''}"
                    data-value="${answer.value}"
                    data-followup="${answer.followup || ''}"
                    data-type="${isFollowupView ? 'followup' : 'main'}"
                >
                    ${answer.text}
                </div>
            `;
        }).join('');

        questionContainer.innerHTML = `
            <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row items-center gap-6 mb-6">
                <div class="w-24 h-24 md:w-32 md:h-32 flex-shrink-0">
                    ${questionData.graphic}
                </div>
                <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-center md:text-left">${questionText}</h2>
            </div>
            <div class="space-y-4">
                ${answersHtml}
            </div>
        `;

        document.querySelectorAll('.answer-option').forEach(option => {
            option.addEventListener('click', handleAnswerSelection);
        });

        updateNavButtons();
    }
    
    // --- EVENT HANDLERS ---
    
    function handleAnswerSelection(e) {
        const selectedOption = e.currentTarget;
        const value = parseInt(selectedOption.dataset.value);
        const followupKey = selectedOption.dataset.followup;
        const type = selectedOption.dataset.type;

        if (!userAnswers[currentPillarIndex]) {
            userAnswers[currentPillarIndex] = {};
        }

        if (type === 'main') {
            // If the main answer changes, reset any potential followup answer
            if (userAnswers[currentPillarIndex].mainValue !== value) {
                delete userAnswers[currentPillarIndex].followupValue;
            }
            userAnswers[currentPillarIndex].mainValue = value;
            userAnswers[currentPillarIndex].followupKey = followupKey;
        } else {
            userAnswers[currentPillarIndex].followupValue = value;
        }
        
        renderQuestion();
    }

    function handleNext() {
        const currentAnswer = userAnswers[currentPillarIndex];
        if (!currentAnswer || !currentAnswer.mainValue) {
            alert("Please select an answer before proceeding!");
            return;
        }
        
        const pillar = assessmentData.pillars[currentPillarIndex];
        const hasFollowup = currentAnswer.followupKey && pillar.followups[currentAnswer.followupKey];
        if(hasFollowup && !currentAnswer.followupValue) {
             alert("Please select an answer for the follow-up question!");
             return;
        }

        if (currentPillarIndex < assessmentData.pillars.length - 1) {
            currentPillarIndex++;
            renderQuestion();
            updateProgress();
            window.scrollTo(0, 0);
        } else {
            showResults();
        }
    }

    function handleBack() {
        if (currentPillarIndex > 0) {
            currentPillarIndex--;
            renderQuestion();
            updateProgress();
            window.scrollTo(0, 0);
        }
    }

    // --- UI UPDATES ---

    function updateProgress() {
        const progressPercentage = ((currentPillarIndex) / assessmentData.pillars.length) * 100;
        progressBar.style.width = `${progressPercentage}%`;
        progressSurfboard.style.left = `${progressPercentage}%`;
    }

    function updateNavButtons() {
        backBtn.classList.toggle('hidden', currentPillarIndex === 0);
        nextBtn.textContent = currentPillarIndex === assessmentData.pillars.length - 1 ? 'See My Vibe' : 'Next';
    }

    // --- RESULTS LOGIC ---

    function showResults() {
        assessmentScreen.classList.add('hidden');
        resultsScreen.classList.remove('hidden');
        window.scrollTo(0, 0);

        const scores = assessmentData.pillars.map((_, index) => {
            const answer = userAnswers[index];
            // Handle case where a question might not have a followup
            if (answer.followupKey && answer.followupValue) {
                return answer.followupValue;
            }
            return answer.mainValue;
        });

        const averageScore = Math.round(scores.reduce((a, b) => a + b, 0) / scores.length);
        const resultData = assessmentData.results.find(r => r.level === averageScore) || assessmentData.results[0];

        document.getElementById('result-title').textContent = resultData.title;
        document.getElementById('result-badge').innerHTML = resultData.badge;
        document.getElementById('result-diagnosis').textContent = resultData.diagnosis;
        document.getElementById('result-funny-image').innerHTML = resultData.funnyImage;
        const playVerbalBtn = document.getElementById('play-verbal-btn');
        
        const newPlayBtn = playVerbalBtn.cloneNode(true);
        playVerbalBtn.parentNode.replaceChild(newPlayBtn, playVerbalBtn);
        newPlayBtn.addEventListener('click', () => playVerbalAssessment(resultData.diagnosis));

        renderRadarChart(scores);
    }

    function playVerbalAssessment(text) {
        if (speechSynthesis.speaking) {
            speechSynthesis.cancel();
            return;
        }
        const utterance = new SpeechSynthesisUtterance(text);
        utterance.lang = 'en-US';
        utterance.rate = 0.9;
        utterance.pitch = 1.1;
        speechSynthesis.speak(utterance);
    }

    function renderRadarChart(scores) {
        const ctx = document.getElementById('results-chart').getContext('2d');
        const labels = assessmentData.pillars.map(p => p.name);

        if (resultsChart) {
            resultsChart.destroy();
        }

        resultsChart = new Chart(ctx, {
            type: 'radar',
            data: {
                labels: labels,
                datasets: [{
                    label: 'Your Vibe',
                    data: scores,
                    backgroundColor: 'rgba(79, 70, 229, 0.4)',
                    borderColor: 'rgba(129, 140, 248, 1)',
                    borderWidth: 2,
                    pointBackgroundColor: 'rgba(129, 140, 248, 1)',
                    pointBorderColor: '#fff',
                    pointHoverBackgroundColor: '#fff',
                    pointHoverBorderColor: 'rgba(129, 140, 248, 1)'
                }]
            },
            options: {
                responsive: true,
                maintainAspectRatio: false,
                scales: {
                    r: {
                        angleLines: { color: 'rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2)' },
                        grid: { color: 'rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2)' },
                        pointLabels: {
                            color: 'white',
                            font: {
                                size: 12,
                                weight: 'bold'
                            }
                        },
                        ticks: {
                            color: 'white',
                            backdropColor: 'rgba(0,0,0,0)',
                            stepSize: 1,
                            font: { size: 10 }
                        },
                        min: 0,
                        max: 5
                    }
                },
                plugins: {
                    legend: {
                        display: false
                    }
                },
                onClick: (e, elements) => {
                    if (elements.length > 0) {
                        const clickedIndex = elements[0].index;
                        showModalForPillar(clickedIndex, scores[clickedIndex]);
                    }
                }
            }
        });
    }
    
    function showModalForPillar(pillarIndex, score) {
        const pillarName = assessmentData.pillars[pillarIndex].name;
        const breakdown = assessmentData.detailedBreakdown[pillarName].find(b => b.level === score);
        
        if(breakdown) {
            modalTitle.textContent = pillarName;
            modalLevel.textContent = `Your Level: ${score} - ${breakdown.title}`;
            modalMeaning.innerHTML = breakdown.meaning;
            modalNextStep.innerHTML = breakdown.next_step;
            
            modal.classList.remove('hidden');
            setTimeout(() => modal.classList.remove('opacity-0'), 10);
        }
    }

    // --- KICK IT OFF ---
    init();
});
</script>

</body>
</html>


